## 1. Purpose
This log is the single record of every business-continuity, disaster-recovery, and backup-restore test performed at [COMPANY]: what was exercised, against which scenario, what RTO/RPO was achieved versus target, what failed, and what corrective actions resulted. It is the evidence that the BCP (`business-continuity-plan.md.template`), the DRP (`disaster-recovery-plan.md.template`), and the Backup Policy (`../operations/backup-policy.md.template`) are operated — not merely written.

## 2. Scope
All planned tests and exercises of continuity and recovery capability within the ISMS scope (`../governance/isms-scope-statement.md.template`): tabletop exercises, functional/simulation tests, region or account failovers, restore-from-backup validations (including [Snowflake] Time Travel/replication tests), and post-incident recovery reviews credited as tests.

## 3. How to Use This Log
1. Schedule tests to satisfy the cadence in the BCP (at least annually) and the Backup Policy (restore tests at least [quarterly]).
2. Append a row for **every** test, including failed or aborted ones — a failed test with tracked corrective actions is good evidence; a gap in the log is a finding.
3. Record **RTO/RPO achieved vs. target** for functional tests; tabletops record scenario and decisions instead.
4. Findings **shall** be tracked to closure in `../governance/corrective-action-poam.md.template`; reference the POA&M ID.
5. Test restores using PHI **shall** note the controlled environment used and confirm post-test data removal (Backup Policy §6).
6. Summarize results at management review (`../governance/management-review.md.template`).

**Test types:** `Tabletop` · `Functional` · `Failover` · `Restore Validation` · `Post-Incident Review`.
**Results:** `Pass` · `Pass with Findings` · `Fail` · `Aborted`.

