## 5. Roles & Responsibilities
| Role | Responsibility |
|---|---|
| [Security Officer / CISO] | Owns the log; verifies test cadence is met; reports results to management review. |
| [Platform Engineering Lead] | Executes functional/restore tests; records RTO/RPO results; maintains runbooks. |
| [BC Coordinator] | Plans and facilitates tabletop exercises; records decisions and findings. |
| Finding Owners | Drive corrective actions to closure in the POA&M. |

See `../governance/roles-and-responsibilities.md.template` for full role definitions.

## 6. Exceptions
Missing a required test window requires documented risk acceptance per `../governance/exceptions-and-waivers.md.template`, approved by the [Security Officer], with the test rescheduled — the cadence requirement re-applies when the exception lapses.

## 7. Compliance, Monitoring & Enforcement
The log is reviewed at internal audit (`../governance/internal-audit-program.md.template`) and management review as primary evidence of HITRUST 12.e and HIPAA testing-and-revision requirements. Overdue tests and unclosed findings are flagged by the [Security Officer] and tracked in the POA&M.

